## How I judge a website's success

Three measures, in order:

1. **Enquiries.** Did the new site generate more buyer contacts than the old one — phone, form, WhatsApp combined. This is the only number that matters for service businesses.
2. **Rankings for the queries that drive enquiries.** Not vanity rankings on long-tail terms. Page-one positions for the queries with commercial intent.
3. **Core Web Vitals + accessibility + indexation.** The technical floor. If these aren't right, the first two won't compound.

I don't optimise for design awards or "engagement" metrics that don't link to revenue. The work is judged on whether the business gets more customers afterwards.

